_Installing IBM TSM client LinuxX86_64 SYSV_
  Required packages
   - gskcrypt64-8.x.x.x.linux.x86_64.rpm
   - gskssl64-8.x.x.x.linux.x86_64.rpm
   - TIVsm-API64.x86_64.rpm
   - TIVsm-BA.x86_64.rpm

  Install 64-bit GSkit
   # rpm -U gskcrypt64-8.x.x.x.linux.x86_64.rpm gskssl64-8.x.x.x.linux.x86_64.rpm

  Install 64-bit TSM API
   # rpm -i TIVsm-API64.x86_64.rpm

  Install TSM backup-archive client components
   # rpm -i TIVsm-BA.x86_64.rpm
  
  Copy provided config files
   # Need to know more about config distibution 

_IBM TSM Backup-Archive cliend CLI_
  Default install directory LINUX: /opt/tivoli/tsm/client/ba/bin
  Default install directory Solaris: /usr/tivoli/tsm/client/ba/bin
  Backup-Archive client CLI: dsmc
		###########################################################
		[john@localhost ~]$ dsmc
		IBM Tivoli Storage Manager
		Command Line Backup-Archive Client Interface
		  Client Version 7, Release 1, Level 0.3
		  Client date/time: 09/12/2014 09:27:09
		(c) Copyright by IBM Corporation and other(s) 1990, 2014. All Rights Reserved.

		Node Name: john-x201.CRISTIE.SE
		Session established with server TSM2: Windows
		  Server Version 7, Release 1, Level 0.100
		  Server date/time: 09/12/2014 09:26:41  Last access: 09/12/2014 09:25:15

		tsm> quit
		############################################################
   
   Help pages are included in dsmc
    $ dsmc help help 
	################
	# 2.21 Help
	# Use the help command to display information about commands, options, and
	# messages.
	#
	# Tip: If you use the help command on the initial command line, no server
	#  contact is made and no password is needed.
	###################################
    $ dsmc help restore
    $ dsmc help incremental
    $ dsmc help selective

   

_Backing up using TSM backup-archive client CLI_
  Scheduled - Tivoli Storage Manager client acceptor daemon service 
   # /etc/init.d/dsmcad {start|stop|restart|status}

  Manually
  - Incremantal backup, backup changed files, file path/filesystem optional parameter
   # cd /opt/tivoli/tsm/client/ba/bin
   # dsmc
   tsm> incremental [/path/to/backup]
    
  - Selective backup (always backup, incl non-changed files)
   # cd /opt/tivoli/tsm/client/ba/bin
   # dsmc 
   tsm> selective </path/to/backup> [option]

_Restoring files using TSM backup-archive client CLI_
  Restore a file examples (dsmc help restore)
   # cd /opt/tivoli/tsm/client/ba/bin
   # dsmc
   -- Restore the most recent version of a deleted file
   tsm> restore /path/to/file.txt -latest 
   -- List all versions of a file, pick one to restore
   tsm> restore /path/to/file.txt -pick -inactive 
   -- Restore file1 to new name and location
   tsm> restore /path/to/file1.txt /path/to/new/dir/file2.txt 
   
  Restore multiple files examples
   # cd /opt/tivoli/tsm/client/ba/bin
   # dsmc
   -- Restore file structure to original location incl subdirectories
   tsm> restore /home/ -subdirs=yes  
   -- Restore many files to new location, trailing / is important if "projects" is a dir, use " " for paths with wildcards 
   tsm> restore "/home/john/Documents/*" /home/glenn/projects/ 
